Certainly! Here's a basic HTML template that you can use as a starting point:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My HTML Template</title>
    <style>
        /* Your CSS styles here */
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    
    <header>
        <!-- Your header content here -->
    </header>
    
    <nav>
        <!-- Your navigation menu here -->
    </nav>
    
    <main>
        <!-- Your main content here -->
    </main>
    
    <footer>
        <!-- Your footer content here -->
    </footer>

    <script>
        // Your JavaScript code here
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

This template includes the basic structure of an HTML document with placeholders for the header, navigation, main content, and footer sections. You can add your CSS styles within the `<style></style>` tags and any JavaScript code between the `<script></script>` tags. Replace the comments with your actual content to complete the template.

Feel free to customize this template according to your needs and add additional HTML elements, styles, or scripts as required.
